# Death Mage Pale Road Abilities
#
# Ability Name		Unique Key						Category of Ability		Type						Source Page						Description
Dirge of Command		KEY:Dirge of Command ~ Corpse Mage		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.SpellLike		SOURCEPAGE:p.17					DESC:You may attempt to control undead creatures you encounter. This functions as the command undead spell, except it only functions on undead with no more than %1 hit dice. You may use this power %2 times per day.|DeathMageLvl|DeathMagePaleRoadTimes
Army of the Dead		KEY:Army of the Dead ~ Corpse Mage		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.17					DESC:You may have a number of undead minions who are totally loyal to you, similar to the Leadership feat.
Eat the Dead		KEY:Eat the Dead ~ Ghoul Mage			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.18					DESC:As a full round action that provokes an attack of opportunity, you can eat part of an adjacent creature of the abberration, animal, dragon, fey, humanoid, magical beast, monstrous humanoid, corporeal undead, or vermin type that diead no longer than %1 rounds ago. This allows you to regain one hit point for every hit die or level possessed by the creature you feast upon. After using this power, you gain a +%2 morale bonus to all attack rolls, saving throws and skill checks for %3 minutes. You may use this power %4 times per day.|DeathMageLvl|1+(DeathMageLvl+1)/11|DeathMageLvl|DeathMagePaleRoadTimes
Sickening Touch		KEY:Sickening Touch ~ Ghoul Mage		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.18					DESC:As a standard action, you can make a target ill by touching it. Using this ability requires a touch attack that forces a living creature to make a Fortitude save (DC%1). On a failed save, the target is sickened for %2 rounds. A neutralize poison spell removes the sickened effect. Creatures that are immune to poison are unaffected. You may use this power %3 times per day.|DeathMagePaleRoadDC|DeathMageLvl|DeathMagePaleRoadTimes
Ghast Touch			KEY:Ghast Touch ~ Ghoul Mage			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.18					DESC:As a standard action, you can paralyze a target by touching it. This is a rouch attack that forces living creatures to make a Fortitude save (DC%1). On a failed save, the target is paralyzed for %2 rounds. At the end of each of its turns, the paralyzed target may make another fortitude save at a -5 penalty to see if its paralysis ends early. You may use this power %3 times per day.|DeathMagePaleRoadDC|DeathMageLvl|DeathMagePaleRoadTimes
Deny Death			KEY:Deny Death ~ Reaper Mage			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.19	BONUS:HP|CURRENTMAX|,TL	DESC:When your hit point total drops beneath 0, you automatically stabilize. You don't die from hp loss until you reach a number of negative hp equal to or greater than %1.|DeathMageLvl/2+CONSCORE
Reap				KEY:Reap ~ Reaper Mage				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.19					DESC:As a swift action and prior to your attack roll, you can empower a melee attack with the certainty of the grave. The attack gains +%1 to hit and +1d6 damage (+2d6 if the target is undead). Empowered attacks count as magic for purposes of bypassing DR. You may use this ability %2 times per day.|min(CHA,DeathMageLvl)|DeathMagePaleRoadTimes
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Reap ~ Reaper Mage.MOD	DESC:As a swift action and prior to your attack roll, you can empower a melee attack with the certainty of the grave. The attack gains +%1 to hit and +2d6 damage (+4d6 if the target is undead). Empowered attacks count as magic for purposes of bypassing DR (and bypass any DR of an undead target). You may use this ability %2 times per day.|min(CHA,DeathMageLvl)|DeathMagePaleRoadTimes|PREVARGTEQ:DeathMageLvl,7
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Reap ~ Reaper Mage.MOD	DESC:As a swift action and prior to your attack roll, you can empower a melee attack with the certainty of the grave. The attack gains +%1 to hit and +3d6 damage (+6d6 if the target is undead). Empowered attacks count as magic for purposes of bypassing DR (and bypass any DR of an undead target, doing full damage to ethereal and incorporeal undead). You may use this ability %2 times per day.|min(CHA,DeathMageLvl)|DeathMagePaleRoadTimes|PREVARGTEQ:DeathMageLvl,14
Protection from Undead	KEY:Protection from Undead ~ Reaper Mage	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.19					DESC:As a move action, you can create a field antithetical to the powers of necromancy and the undead. The field is centered on you, moves with you, and has a 20-foot radius. While within this field, all creatures gain a +%1 deflection bonus to AC and a +%1 resistance bonus to saving throws against all attacks and spells from undead creatures and any necromancy spell. This field last %2 minutes, and you may use it %3 times per day.|CHA|DeathMageLvl|DeathMagePaleRoadTimes
Shape Shadow		KEY:Shape Shadow ~ Shadow Mage		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.20					DESC:You gain the benefit of presistent pretidigitation, unseen servant, and spectral hand as a result of your ability to shape and command shadows.
Shadow Adept		KEY:Shadow Adept ~ Shadow Mage		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.20					DESC:Whenever you cast a shadow conjuration or shadow evocation spell from the death mage spell list, you may use it to emulate any cleric, bard or sorcerer/wizard spell from the conjuration or evocation (as appropriate) schools.
Summon Shadow		KEY:Summon Shadow ~ Shadow Mage		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.20					DESC:You gain the ability to summon three shadows or greater shadows to serve you. This acts as a summon monster V spell, except it always summons three shadows or greater shadows (you choose), the shadows are of your alignment, and the effect has a duration of %1 minutes. You may use this ability %2 times per day.|DeathMageLvl|DeathMagePaleRoadTimes|PREVARGTEQ:DeathMageLvl,16
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Summon Shadow ~ Shadow Mage.MOD	DESC:You gain the ability to summon three shadows to serve you. This acts as a summon monster V spell, except it always summons three shadows, the shadows are of your alignment, and the effect has a duration of %1 minutes. You may use this ability %2 times per day.|DeathMageLvl|DeathMagePaleRoadTimes
Calm of the Grave		KEY:Calm of the Grave ~ Tomb Mage		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.18					DESC:You are immune to any pain or fear effect, as well as the shaken condition.
Terrible Visage		KEY:Terrible Visage ~ Tomb Mage		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.18					DESC:Once per day as a standard action, your can give yourself the appearance of a horrible apparition. You gain a gaze attack, forcing foes that can see you to make a Will save (DC%1). This is a mind-affecting fear gaze attack. A foe that is shaken as a result of this ability becomes immune to it for 24 hours after their shaken condition ends. Your terrible visage remains active for %2 rounds, though you may dismiss it as a free action if you wish.|DeathMagePaleRoadDC|DeathMageLvl
Word of Pain		KEY:Word of Pain ~ Tomb Mage			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.18					DESC:As a standard action, you may say a terrible word of pain to a creature that is able to hear you, and is within 30 feet. The target must make a Fortitude save (DC%1) or be overcome by wracking pain. The pain is so intense that the target becomes confused for %2 rounds. The target receives a new Will save at the end of each of its turns. You may use the word of pain %3 times per day.|DeathMagePaleRoadDC|DeathMageLvl|DeathMageLvl/4-1

